result.execSummary:
The defendant Myrio Rogers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Firearm-Convicted of a Felony, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Myrio Rogers in Court, in custody.  Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask in Court for Myrio Rogers.  Attorney Owen M Piotrowski in Court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in Court for Sentencing hearing with Defendant's other Case, 22CF1060. Court reviewed Character Reference Letters and Defense Pre-Sentence Investigation. State complied with Victim Notification. Statements by the State, Defense, and Defendant. Additional Statements by: Constance R. and Kahdija R. 

AS TO COUNT 1:  
Court sentenced the Defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of FOUR (4) YEARS, Consecutive to Case 22CF1060, with credit for ZERO DAYS time served. 
The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is TWO (2) YEARS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is TWO (2) YEARS. 
 
Court found Defendant is NOT ELIGIBLE for the Challenge Incarceration Program. 
Court found Defendant is ELIGIBLE for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program. 
 
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
- Mental Health Evaluation, comply with recommended treatment and take all prescribed medications. 
- AODA Assessment, comply with recommended treatment. 
- No Contact Order with Israel M. (date of birth 11-30-2000).
- No Contact Order with Constance R. (date of birth 04-30-1977).  
- Obtain/Maintain Full-Time Employment.

Court set Restitution at ZERO. 

Court ordered Defendant to provide a DNA SAMPLE and pay DNA SURCHARGE, payable from Defendant's prison funds at a percentage to be determined by the Department of Corrections (DOC). Remainder to be paid during the period of Extended Supervision. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. CASH BAIL FROM CASE 22CF1060 TO APPLY. 

Court WAIVED COSTS/FEES due to Indigency. 

Court advised Defendant that he is prohibited from firearm possession, ammunition or body armor.
Court advised Defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote until his civil rights are restored.
Court advised Defendant of his right to seek postconviction relief.

FILED: Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief; PreTrial Incarceration Credit; and Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence.
Defense Sentencing Report; received, filed, and forwarded to the Judge for review.

Defendant Myrio Rogers in Court with Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Defendant Myrio Rogers in custody.  Owen M Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Case in Court for Plea hearing. Defendant has THREE CASES in Branch 46: 21CF1775, 22CF1060, and 22CF1061. Discussion placed on the record. Parties have reached a resolution in this matter. State complied with Victim Notification. Plea hearing proceeded. Negotiations placed on the record, and confirmed by Defense and Defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 1: 
Defendant changed his plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to the plea, and advised of Constitutional Rights and maximum penalties. Defendant advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found Defendant knowingly, voluntarily, and intelligently waived all his rights. Parties stipulated to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis for the plea. Court found Defendant GUILTY as charged in the Information, and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction. 

AS TO COUNT 2: 
Pursuant to negotiations and on Motion of the State, Court ordered COUNT 2 DISMISSED BUT READ-IN for the purpose of Sentencing. 

Court advised Defendant that he is prohibited from firearm possession, ammunition, or body armor. 
Court advised Defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and he may not vote until his civil rights are restored. 
Court VACATED Jury Trial date. 

Court ordered case adjourned for Sentencing hearing, Branch 46. Hearing will be held in Room 113 of the Safety Building.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 10:30 am.
